This paper deals with a problem in reinforcement learning, specifically inverse reinforcement learning, where the agent has to act on behalf of a human. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
